name: Fish
properties: Fish are high in omega-3. It also contains alpha-linolenic acid (ALA) provides two essential fatty acids: eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA), and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA). EPA and DHA regulate neurotransmitters, reduce inflammation, and promote healthy brain function.

name: Green Tea
properties: It contains an amino acid called theanine. Theanine has anti-anxiety and calming effects and may increase the production of serotonin and dopamine.

name: Pumpkin Seeds
properties: Good source of potassium, which helps reduce symptoms of stress and anxiety and Zinc helpful for brain and nerve development.

name: Garlic
properties: Antioxidants neutralize free radicals, may reduce or even help prevent some of the damage the free radicals cause over time.

name: Spinach
properties: Spinach contains folate, which produces dopamine, a pleasure-inducing brain chemical, helping you keep calm.

name: Salmon
properties: The omega-3 fatty acids in salmon have anti-inflammatory properties that may help counteract the negative effects of stress hormones.

name: Blueberries
properties: The antioxidants and phytonutrients found in berries fight in your defense, helping improve your body's response to stress and fight stress-related free radicals.

name: Flax Seeds
properties: Great sources of magnesium, it regulates emotions. Magnesium helps in alleviates depression, fatigue, and irritability.

name: Cashew nut
properties: It contains Zinc, an essential mineral that may help reduce anxiety. Zinc affects the levels of a nerve chemical that influences mood.
